            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>
                    To [Marcus] A[g]rius Proculus, son of Marcus, of tribe Voltinia, aedile, quinquennial duovir, quaestor, in the same year flamen of the divine Nerva [and] patron of the municipium. Tullia Me[v]ia Prisca, daughter of Marcus, his mother, [set this up] for her best (and) most dutiful son, my lord. This place was given by decree of the decurions.
                </p>
